\begin_layout Standard
I use pairwise likelihood ratio tests to compare each nested model with
 the full model.
 Those results suggest that Model (4), with year effects and the log violence
 and log public opinion coefficients, is the best fit, so the rest of the
 results proceed using that model.
 Model (4) is also the best according to its AIC value; however, the BIC
 and the log likelihood values identify models (2) and (1), respectively.
 Per the likelihood ratio test results, I proceed with the full model, (4).
 (A full table of all four models' results is included for reference; however,
 we are interested in the transition probabilities rather than the coefficients
 in the table.)
\end_layout

